<dec f='include/unicode/decimfmt.h' l='1473' type='void icu_66::DecimalFormat::setPadCharacter(const icu_66::UnicodeString &amp; padChar)'/>
<doc f='include/unicode/decimfmt.h' l='1459'>/**
     * Set the character used to pad to the format width.  If padding
     * is not enabled, then this will take effect if padding is later
     * enabled.
     * @param padChar a string containing the pad character. If the string
     * has length 0, then the pad character is set to &apos; &apos;.  Otherwise
     * padChar.char32At(0) will be used as the pad character.
     * @see #setFormatWidth
     * @see #getFormatWidth
     * @see #getPadCharacterString
     * @see #getPadPosition
     * @see #setPadPosition
     * @stable ICU 2.0
     */</doc>
